And You Will Know Us By The Trail Of Dead's new album has been put back until January, and will not be released on October the 5th as originally planned. kill me now please.

they are planning a UK tour though. wahey!!

x

in a fit of rage (well, it was more like tidiness) i have deleted all my old journal entries, and i changed the colours. you like? today my parents left for italy for 10 days. of course, i'm having a party. it's practically my right - they are leaving my sister and i alone in the house, after all, it's only fair that i repay their kindness by inviting 20+ drunken 17/18 year olds over. plus, i'm doing all their random jobs like watering plants and doing the wash and so on, i'll need a bit of respite by the end of the week... have just realised that im working 9-4 on results day. schiesse. and none of the other casuals have emailed me back yet, saying 'why of course i will cover your shift, in fact, let me do all of your shifts, you go out and enjoy yourself'... i live in hope. made Tom W a twee indie/post-rock cd. now i need a suitably indie name for it! i'm thinking Cellar Door, or Of Mixtapes and Melodies, but none of them seem quite right. help! xx
